# Layer 2 ‚Äî Research / Plan Execution

> Notion v5 ¬ß"Layer 2 ‚Äî Research / Plan Execution" (lines 446-455).
> Owned by the `task-orchestrator` subagent
> (see `subagents/task-orchestrator.md`).
> Default cadence: every 20 min, driven by `/loop`.
>
> This file is the canonical template shipped by bubble-ops-loop's
> `skills/department-onboarding-guide/templates/layer_2_prompt.md.template`.
> Live fixtures keep a synced copy at `layers/2/PROMPT.md` (pushed via the
> token-broker + git-guard chain ‚Äî never edited directly in the live clone).

## Mission

Read the day's queue items from `queues/research/`. For each, spawn a
dedicated sub-task subagent that runs the relevant skill (per
`dept.yaml::skills.layer_2`) and either:

- emits a **gate** (`queues/gates/<id>.yaml`) when human validation is
  required, OR
- files an **improvement proposal** (`queues/improvements/<id>.yaml`)
  when no human decision is needed and the work can land directly in
  tomorrow's Layer 1 input set.

## Inputs

- `queues/research/*.yaml` ‚Äî queue items materialized by Layer 1
- `outputs/<today>/1/summary.md` ‚Äî context: what Layer 1 said about the day
- `dept.yaml::gate_policies` ‚Äî for each queue item kind, look up which gate
  policy applies (`echo_action`, `mandate_breach_escalation`, etc.) plus
  the `authorization_band` that scopes which instances are eligible

## Process

For each item in `queues/research/`:

1. Read the item; validate against `queue-item.schema.yaml` (operator-side).
2. **Spawn `task-orchestrator` subagent per item** with a focused prompt
   (one item, one skill, one decision-or-proposal).
3. The sub-subagent runs the skill (for the fixture: `echo-skill`).
4. Skill output ‚Üí write to `outputs/<today>/2/research/<item-id>.md`.
5. Decide: gate or improvement?
   - **If `dept.yaml::gate_policies.<kind>.current_mode == manual_required`**
     ‚Üí emit `queues/gates/<item-id>.yaml` (validates against
     `gate-item.schema.yaml` v3 ‚Äî see skeleton below).
   - **Else** ‚Üí emit `queues/improvements/<item-id>.yaml` for Layer 1
     tomorrow.
6. Once an item is consumed, move it out of `queues/research/` (delete
   or rename with `.consumed` suffix).
7. **After the tick has committed + pushed** (STEP E in the `/loop`
   prompt), invoke the gate notification primitive **once per gate
   created this tick**:
   ```bash
   python3 /home/claude/agents/fixture/tools/notify-gate/notify.py \
       --gate-path queues/gates/<id>.yaml \
       --repo bubble-ops-fixture \
       --commit-sha "$(git rev-parse HEAD)" \
       --repo-root /home/claude/agents/fixture
   ```
   The tool reads `FIXTURE_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` (preferred) or
   `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` (fallback) from env, formats a Markdown message
   with gate id / kind / risk / GitHub blob URL / the 4 actions
   (`approve|reject|modify|defer`), and POSTs to @bubtiktikbot ‚Üí
   chat {{OPERATOR_CHAT_ID}} ({{OPERATOR}}). The token is never logged. On Telegram
   failure the tool exits non-zero but does NOT abort the tick ‚Äî the
   gate is already on GitHub, the kanban is the source of truth, the
   notification is a courtesy.

## Gate item v3 ‚Äî required shape

Every gate written to `queues/gates/<id>.yaml` MUST conform to
`schemas-draft/gate-item.schema.yaml` v3. The following 9 root-level
fields are REQUIRED on every gate:

- `id` ‚Äî kebab-case unique identifier, e.g. `gate-research-001`.
- `kind` ‚Äî one of the documented enums OR a `domain:<snake_case>`
  free-form value. Allowed values:
    - v1 internal kinds: `decision`, `exec_retry`, `mandate_breach`, `modify`
    - v3 documented domain kinds: `prospect_dm`, `prospect_followup`,
      `trade_order`, `content_publish`
    - free-form domain escape hatch: `domain:<snake_case>` (e.g.
      `domain:research_decision`, `domain:legal_review`)
  Do NOT invent bare names like `research_decision` ‚Äî they violate both
  the enum and the `^domain:[a-z][a-z_]+$` pattern.
- `source_layer` ‚Äî integer 1..4, layer that emitted the gate
  (Layer 2 ‚Üí `2`).
- `target_layer` ‚Äî integer 1..4, layer that consumes the resolution
  (Layer 2 ‚Üí Layer 3 hand-off ‚Üí `3`).
- `risk_level` ‚Äî one of `low | medium | high | critical`.
- `requires_human` ‚Äî boolean, default `true` for v1 (every gate is
  `manual_required`).
- `actions` ‚Äî non-empty subset of `[approve, reject, modify, defer]`,
  unique, no duplicates.
- `current_mode` ‚Äî autonomy mode AT EMIT-TIME, snapshot value, MUST be
  one of the 5 OFFICIAL modes (Notion v5 lines 256-260):
    - `manual_required` (default for every new dept at eclosure)
    - `manual_unless_policy_passed`
    - `auto_if_policy_passed`
    - `auto_with_veto_window`
    - `disabled`
  Do NOT use any informal shorthand outside this enum ‚Äî shorthand like
  "shadow-autonomy" / "full-autonomy" abstractions lose the doctrine's
  nuance (each official mode encodes a specific human-AI control split).
- `future_eligible_modes` ‚Äî array of modes this gate could eventually
  be raised to, drawn from the same 5-mode enum. May be empty for
  internal-kind gates intended to stay `manual_required` forever.

CONDITIONALLY REQUIRED when `kind` is NOT one of the 4 internal kinds
(i.e. it is a documented domain kind or a `domain:*` free-form):

- `gate_policy_id` ‚Äî links to `dept.yaml::gate_policies.<id>`.
- `authorization_band_id` ‚Äî identifies the dept-domain authorization
  band that scopes which instances of this action class are eligible
  for autonomy (e.g. `maya_warm_prospect_band`).

## Gate skeleton example (copy + adapt per item)

```yaml
# queues/gates/gate-research-001.yaml
id: gate-research-001
kind: domain:research_decision        # OR `decision` for the internal kind
source_layer: 2
target_layer: 3                       # 2 if the resolution loops back to L2
risk_level: low                       # one of: low | medium | high | critical
requires_human: true                  # v1 default; every gate is manual
actions:                              # non-empty subset, unique
  - approve
  - reject
  - modify
  - defer
current_mode: manual_required         # snapshot at emit-time; 5-mode enum
future_eligible_modes:                # subset of the same 5-mode enum
  - auto_with_veto_window
  - auto_if_policy_passed
gate_policy_id: echo_action           # REQUIRED when kind is a domain kind
authorization_band_id: default_band   # REQUIRED when kind is a domain kind
# --- payload (additionalProperties: true at root) -----------------------
summary: |
  E2E round-trip validation complete. Layer 2 processed
  research-roundtrip-test-001 successfully. Awaiting human sign-off.
evidence:
  - outputs/2026-05-20/2/research/research-roundtrip-test-001.md
  - outputs/2026-05-20/2/summary.md
created_at: 2026-05-20T18:44:13Z
```

The 5 official autonomy modes again, for searchability and so any future
audit-grep finds them in one place:

- `manual_required`
- `manual_unless_policy_passed`
- `auto_if_policy_passed`
- `auto_with_veto_window`
- `disabled`

## Outputs (the 4-file schema ‚Äî per Notion v5 ¬ß"Output layer")

Write ALL FOUR files under `outputs/<today>/2/`:

| File | Content |
|---|---|
| `outputs/<today>/2/summary.md` | Narrative: items processed, gates created, improvements filed |
| `outputs/<today>/2/artifacts/.gitkeep` | Placeholder (per-item research briefs land here as `<id>.md`) |
| `outputs/<today>/2/logs.jsonl` | One JSON line per item processed: `{ts, item_id, decision, target_file}` |
| `outputs/<today>/2/.last-run` | ISO timestamp of this tick's completion |

Plus gates: `queues/gates/<item-id>.yaml` (one per gating decision).

## Side-effects

- `git add outputs/<today>/2/ queues/gates/ queues/improvements/ queues/research/`
- Commit message: `layer-2: N items processed, M gates, K improvements`.
- Push (via `/opt/bubble-git-guard/bin/bubble-git-guard push`).
- **Telegram ping per gate** via the `notify-gate` primitive
  (`tools/notify-gate/notify.py`) ‚Äî see step 7 above. Each gate fires
  exactly one notification. The token never appears in logs.

## Perm policy (recap)

The `task-orchestrator` has `Agent` in its toolset (it spawns sub-task
subagents) and `permissionMode: acceptEdits`. Write paths must stay within
`outputs/*/2/` + `queues/gates/` + `queues/improvements/` + the cleanup of
consumed items in `queues/research/`.
